  "taxGuideIntroTitle": "How to complete the Tax System setup?",
  "taxGuideIntroDescription": "This guide walks through the entire integration flow with the Iranian Taxpayers System in the new Hesabix version—from key generation to data quality checks and invoice submission.",
  "taxGuidePrereqTitle": "Prerequisites before you begin",
  "taxGuidePrereqItem1": "Access to the “Tax System” menu as a business admin",
  "taxGuidePrereqItem2": "Accurate registration data (national ID, economic code, corporate email)",
  "taxGuidePrereqItem3": "Active access to your taxpayer workspace on my.tax.gov.ir",
  "taxGuideStep1Title": "1) Generate keys inside Hesabix",
  "taxGuideStep1Description": "Use the “Generate new keys” card to create the private/public key pair and CSR.",
  "taxGuideStep1Bullet1": "Open the Keys & Certificates tab and tap the generate button.",
  "taxGuideStep1Bullet2": "Provide the exact taxpayer type and national ID.",
  "taxGuideStep1Bullet3": "Persian/English names and email must match the tax records.",
  "taxGuideStep2Title": "2) Download and store securely",
  "taxGuideStep2Description": "Keys are shown only once; store them safely.",
  "taxGuideStep2Bullet1": "Download the key files and keep them in offline, encrypted storage.",
  "taxGuideStep2Bullet2": "Never share the private key outside the tax integration team.",
  "taxGuideStep2Bullet3": "If the private key is lost you must regenerate the entire pair.",
  "taxGuideStep3Title": "3) Register the public key on my.tax.gov.ir",
  "taxGuideStep3Description": "You must upload the Public Key to obtain the tax memory ID.",
  "taxGuideStep3Bullet1": "Log into my.tax.gov.ir and navigate to Case Access > Enrollment > Tax Memory ID.",
  "taxGuideStep3Bullet2": "Select “By taxpayer” and upload the generated Public Key file.",
  "taxGuideStep3Bullet3": "Copy the issued memory ID and paste it back into Hesabix.",
  "taxGuideStep4Title": "4) Complete the connection form in Hesabix",
  "taxGuideStep4Description": "Tax memory ID, economic code and private key are mandatory under the Connection tab.",
  "taxGuideStep4Bullet1": "Enter the ID and economic code without extra spaces.",
  "taxGuideStep4Bullet2": "Paste the PEM private key and optionally store the Public Key and CSR.",
  "taxGuideStep4Bullet3": "Enable sandbox mode only for staging/testing environments.",
  "taxGuideStep5Title": "5) Request the intermediate certificate via CSR",
  "taxGuideStep5Description": "Legal entities must submit the CSR to the national certificate authority.",
  "taxGuideStep5Bullet1": "Visit gica.ir and choose the CSR-based request option.",
  "taxGuideStep5Bullet2": "Fill in the company details and pay the issuance fee.",
  "taxGuideStep5Bullet3": "After in-person verification upload the issued certificate into Hesabix.",
  "taxGuideStep6Title": "6) Assign product/service tax codes",
  "taxGuideStep6Description": "Invoices will be rejected if items lack tax code and unit.",
  "taxGuideStep6Bullet1": "Edit each item under Products & Services and add the 13-digit tax code.",
  "taxGuideStep6Bullet2": "Use the public code list from stuffid.tax.gov.ir or request dedicated codes.",
  "taxGuideStep6Bullet3": "Service codes can be obtained from portal.gs1-ir.org.",
  "taxGuideStep7Title": "7) Run data quality checks before submission",
  "taxGuideStep7Description": "Review the Data Quality tab and the tax workspace before sending invoices.",
  "taxGuideStep7Bullet1": "The Data Quality tab highlights missing fields for products, customers and invoices.",
  "taxGuideStep7Bullet2": "Add invoices to the tax workspace first and fix validation errors inline.",
  "taxGuideStep7Bullet3": "Send single or bulk invoices only after the checklist is green.",
